<main class="main-content pillar-community">

  <section class="section-block">
    <h1 class="section-heading">TGK Community</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A gathering place for readers, seekers, contrarians, and builders of The Gnostic Key.
      Here, arguments are sharpened, assumptions tested, and interpretations refined through
      disciplined, respectful dialogue.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="community-charter section-block">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Community Ethos</h2>
    <p>
      The TGK Community rests on one foundational principle:
      <strong>we seek truth through clarity, not dominance.</strong>
      We engage arguments, not identities. We steelman before we critique.
    </p>

    <ul class="rules-list">
      <li>No doxxing or targeted harassment.</li>
      <li>Critique institutions, systems, and public power, not private citizens.</li>
      <li>No calls for violence of any kind.</li>
      <li>Pseudonyms encouraged. Real names not required.</li>
      <li>Good faith is the expected baseline. Bad faith is structurally discouraged.</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="muted small">
      Commenting requires sign-in with email. You may choose any pseudonym.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="community-modules section-block">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Community Spaces</h2>

    <div class="community-grid">
      {% for m in communityModules %}
        <div class="community-card {{ m.state }}">
          <div class="community-card-glyph">{{ m.glyph }}</div>
          <h3 class="community-card-title">{{ m.title }}</h3>
          <p class="community-card-desc">{{ m.desc }}</p>

          <p class="community-card-meta small">
            Tier: <strong>{{ m.tier | upper }}</strong>
            {% if m.state == "coming-soon" %}
              <span class="coming-soon-tag">Coming Soon</span>
            {% endif %}
          </p>
        </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>

      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-block">
    <h2 class="section-heading">The Steel Man Principle</h2>
    <p>
      Every reply within the community begins with a simple requirement:
      <strong>“What is the argument you are responding to, in your own words?”</strong>
      This ensures that clarity precedes criticism, and understanding precedes disagreement.
    </p>
    <p>
      This is not merely a rule, but a cultural signature that defines the TGK Community.
    </p>
  </section>

</main>
